{"title_page": "Renaissance Magazine", "text_new": "{{short description|American magazine about renaissance related topics}}\n{{Infobox Magazine\n| title = Renaissance Magazine\n| image_file =Renaissance Magazine.gif\n| image_size = 150px\n| image_caption =\n| editor = Adam Eyler & Tanya Laird\n| editor_title =\n| frequency = Bi-monthly\n| circulation = 35,000\n| category =\n| company = Lionheart Entertainment LLC\n| publisher = \n| founded = 1996\n| firstdate =\n| country = United States\n| based = Houston, Texas\n| language = [[English language|English]]\n| website = [http://www.renaissancemagazine.com]\n| issn = 1088-906X\n}}\n'''''Renaissance Magazine''''' is a glossy [[United States|American]] magazine published bimonthly. Each issue comprises approximately 90 pages, and includes articles about the contemporary [[renaissance fair]]e experience, medieval and renaissance history, castles, heraldry, cooking, and interviews with key individuals in the renaissance fair industry. It was founded in 1996 by \"Lady Kimberly,\" a graduate of [[Yale University]], and has its headquarters in [[Bridgeport, Connecticut]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Renaissance Magazine|url=http://us-ct.bizdirlib.com/m/node/31445|work=Connecticut Business Database|accessdate=15 November 2015}}</ref> The magazine is owned by Lionheart Entertainment LLC in Houston, Texas. \n\nThe magazine is the sponsor of the Annual Renaissance Festival Awards together with ''Celtic Music'' magazine.<ref>{{cite news|title=Winners of the 7th Annual Renaissance Festival Awards of 2011|url=http://renaissancefestivalmusic.com/2012/7th-annual-renaissance-festival-awards-of-2011/|accessdate=15 November 2015|work=Renaissance Festival Podcast|date=1 March 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117021531/http://renaissancefestivalmusic.com/2012/7th-annual-renaissance-festival-awards-of-2011/|archivedate=17 November 2015}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official|http: